Vice President Mike Pence addressed the National Federation of Independent Business (NFIB) in Washington, D.C., thanking them for their support in the 2016 election and discussing the Trump administration's efforts to repeal and replace Obamacare. Pence also spoke about the administration's commitment to cutting taxes and reducing regulations on small businesses. He emphasized the importance of small businesses to the American economy and praised their resilience and determination. Pence expressed confidence that the Senate would take the necessary steps to repeal and replace Obamacare and promised that the administration would work with Congress to pass significant tax cuts. He encouraged NFIB members to continue advocating for the president's agenda and to have faith in the future of America.